The percentage for a successful reinforcement is off... by a lot. Usually by half and get worse the lower the percentage gets. 33% is closer to 20%, 10% is closer to 5%. The additional +1% for each failure doesn't work at all. You have a better chance to win at roulette in Vegas than having proper % rolls to reinforce your gear.

This game is too good for its price. You get heroes, upgrade them and their gear, grind dungeons, PvP, chat with a friendly community. Its a game where you can progress faster with real money but it is not required to spend a dime whatsoever. You get gems by playing the game. Pvp rewards are huge and pve likewise. The store advertisiement for gems is great it maxes out to 40. Negative reviews are degenerates and noobs who cant play character progression games. :) 11/10

Why does Autolevel count down even when it's deactivated? Why are hero promotion materials so rare? Why do hero promotion materials cost so much? An alright game. Graphics are okay, gameplay is idle oriented with 3 cornucopias worth of mechanics to monitor/regulate. Overwhelming even with the miniscule tutorial trying to explain it all. Subpar premium currency rewards(not very f2p friendly.) Just too busy, too much to juggle, and too plain looking to find enjoyable personally.

Helped me realize my displeasure of idle games. I will just stick to games where *I* am playing the game, not the auto pilot. Also I don't know how this is supposed to be an RPG, as I do not see any role-playing on my end. Sure there are hero classes, but they do not feel different from each other. Plus there were a couple annoying bugs for me, but those did not really impact my experience as much as the other issues.

Shop is VERY expensive for the gain, which is good/bad, definitely reduces the p2w. Still missing a lot of content present on other version on older servers. The 3k gem cost for a guild is absurd. No freebies to start, which is also good/bad. There's also a coupon available to download this for free, encourage others to use coupon if wanting to try this game. It's very strategic and f2p can do extremely well if smart. Will up rating once content restored.
